cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CR 

The paper discusses the susceptibility of deep learning models to adversarial examples and proposes a deep sparse coding model as a potential solution. This topic falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Given that the paper focuses on the robustness of classifiers, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI and cs.NE, which also deal with machine learning and neural networks. Cs.CR is less likely but still relevant as it deals with security and adversarial attacks.
